2. cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) - The paper uses a human cognitive model to build an inter-keystroke timing dictionary, which suggests that the paper may also belong to the Human-Computer Interaction sub-category. 
3. cs.CY (Computers and Society) - The paper discusses the potential threat of the proposed attack method to real-world applications, which may fall under the Computers and Society sub-category. 
4. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) - The paper uses a cognitive model to build a dictionary, which may also suggest that the paper belongs to the Artificial Intelligence sub-category. 
5. cs.LG (Machine Learning) - The paper uses a small amount of training data to determine the parameters of the cognitive model, which may also suggest that the paper belongs to the Machine Learning sub-category.
